CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 6, 1953, pg. 6, reads: "Platform Guests at Baptist Meet - Prominent women of the city graced the platform Monday night in Central Baptist Church at the first Leadership Institute, sponsored by the Baptist Daughters of the West. Pictured, left to right, they are Mrs. Nellie West, Mrs. Alma Illery, Mrs. Lucy Mickey, the Rev. A. Amos Brackeen, Mrs. Cornell E. Talley, Mrs. S. L. Spear, Mrs. A. B. Barnes and Mrs. O. J. Martin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left, Nellie West, Alma Illery, Lucy Mickey, Rev. A. Amos Brackeen, Martha Talley, Mrs. S. L. Spear, Mrs. A. B. Barnes, and Mrs. O. J. Martin, posed in Central Baptist Church
